              . The longitudinal rolls are parallel to the primary rolls and the transverse rolls are orthogonal to the primary rolls, and both result in striped patterns. The oblique rolls lead to the formation of convection cells with aspect ratio dictated by their inclination angle and formation of rhombic patterns. Two mechanisms of instability have been identified. In the case of
              
                
                  
